author: Laura McCallister
title: ALCS schedule dates, times announced
text:
ALCS schedule dates, times announced Posted: Updated: Thursday, October 15 2015 12:40 AM EDT 2015-10-15 04:40:26 GMT Johnny Cueto delivered a masterpiece on his biggest stage yet, pitching eight dominant innings Wednesday night and leading the never-say-die Kansas City Royals to a 7-2 victory over the Houston Astros and back to... More > Johnny Cueto knew the Kansas City Royals had wagered much of their future on him, trading away a bevy of prospects in late July so that he could pitch in moments like this. More > KANSAS CITY, MO (KCTV) - 
Here are the dates and times of the American League Championship Series. 
On Friday the Kansas City Royals face off against the Toronto Blue Jays. First pitch is at 7:07 p.m. for game 1 at Kauffman Stadium. 
On Saturday the two teams meet up for game 2 at Kauffman Stadium. First pitch is at 3:07 p.m. 
On Monday, ALCS game 3 will be at Rogers Centre in Toronto. First pitch is at 7:07 p.m. 
Check back with this story for remaining ALCS schedule times as they will be announced at a later date.
